Subject: FEATURE: add support for non-disabling to LPN to SystemVerilog
Date: Tue, 30 Nov 2010 10:45:28 -0700
X-Mailer: Apple Mail (2.936)

To add support for non-disabling to LPN to SystemVerilog translater,  
consider the following example:

p0 - {e0}[d0]<a0> -> t0
p0 - {e1}[d1]<a1> -> t1

always@ (posedge(e0) or p0)
	t0 = (e0 & p0)

assign #delay(d0) t0p = t0

always@ (posedge(t0p)
	p0 = false
	<a0>

This may not be quite correct, so it will need to be checked with  
simulation.
  

